api-1  | What excites you about a career in engineering/technology? Why do you think your abilities and skills are a good fit for
api-1  | Plaksha's B.Tech program?
api-1  | My interest in technology has grown over the years. My first tryst with computers was probably in Grade 4 when it was introduced in our
api-1  | school curriculum. This curriculum, entailing foundational coding languages like QBasic and Scratch, piqued my interest and I tried to develop
api-1  | a simple arithmetic calculator. This interest was further strengthened when my chess coach told me that computer programs could outsmart
api-1  | humans. Intrigued by this notion, I spent months trying to comprehend algorithms behind these programs. My penchant for mathematics
api-1  | from my formative days was another factor that drew me towards this futuristic domain. Apart from being my top-scoring subject, I enjoyed
api-1  | the challenge of participating and excelling in competitions like the SOF Olympiad and UNSW.
api-1  | My exposure expanded through participation in national competitions like IJSO, international trips (NASA, Silicon Valley, and the Hadron
api-1  | Collider at CERN), and industry internships. Multiple internships helped me understand Indian IT landscape, and reinforced the importance of
api-1  | sophisticated computing technologies for continued innovation and exploration. These experiences reinforced my desire to pursue graduation
api-1  | in the field of computers.
api-1  | Driven by a strong desire to develop academic rigour, I embarked on the preparation for one of the most challenging examinations in the
api-1  | world- the JEE Advanced. This examination tests not only mathematical prowess but also analytical capabilities. Over the past two years, I
api-1  | have dedicated myself to an intensive study regimen, solving intricate problems and tackling baffling concepts from calculus to mechanics.
api-1  | The journey has been demanding, yet it has equipped me with invaluable skills that are beneficial in understanding algorithms, data
api-1  | structures, and software development. Additionally, I have enhanced my technical acumen by studying Java and Html and also secured Rank
api-1  | 2 in Grade 11 at my school.
api-1  | Focusing on personality and leadership development, I have participated in the student council and various inter-school events over the last
api-1  | four years. My interest in Speech and Drama enabled me to complete Grade 7 at Trinity College, London. I have also actively engaged in
api-1  | many non-profit activities such as waste collection drives and beach clean-ups.
api-1  | Cumulatively, my journey has crystallised my desire to pursue graduation in computer science. I intend to follow-up with higher education
api-1  | and industry experience at leading global firms to contribute meaningfully to the society and field of science.
api-1  | I believe that studying at a modern and state-of-the-art university like Plaksha would help me realize my ambitions.
api-1  | Share a time when you contributed to a project or activity that positively affected your school or community. What
api-1  | challenges did you face, and what did you learn about leadership and perseverance?
api-1  | The importance of social responsibility and community involvement had been emphasized time and again in my school since early days.
api-1  | However, initially I was oblivious to its true meaning till I undertook the SignBee project by V-shesh Foundation. I came to know about V-
api-1  | shesh from my classmates in the 10th grade. This project entailed learning Sign Language which is imperative for communicating with the
api-1  | differently-abled and creating awareness about the same in society.
api-1  | The initial phase of this project was interesting and informative as I imbibed a plethora of symbols and understood the intricacies of the
api-1  | language. As we moved to the practical phase, we were required to perform a short story for the differently-abled kids. This was an eye-
api-1  | opener for me in terms of real challenges involved in converting theory to practice and taught me various lessons like empathy, gratitude,
api-1  | compassion and responsibility. Towards the end of the project, I made an online presentation to educate people of my locality about the sign
api-1  | language and this helped me implement by learnings on wider scope.
api-1  | I organized workshops and sessions in my society to sensitize people on this topic and make people understand that how simple uses of sign
api-1  | language can help the differently-abled people feel more inclusive in our society. Reception to this idea was lukewarm at first as most people
api-1  | seemed unwilling to make an effort to learn the language. I had to go through several iterations like organizing personalized sessions over
api-1  | weekends and using different pneumonic tools to make sign language easy to learn and assimilate. To my surprise, the younger generation
api-1  | was more enthusiastic about learning. This required me to involve my family who could put forth the ideas in a better way than I could
api-1  | envisage.
api-1  | I was extremely satisfied that I was able to contribute in a small yet meaningful way towards the society over a span of two months.
api-1  | Predominantly, I learnt about leadership and how it requires one to approach a situation from different avenues and emerge with new ideas
api-1  | and have the passion to keep going through tough times. It also required motivating my colleagues several times who helped me during
api-1  | execution.
api-1  | Today, I look back at the Signbee experience as one that made a better human being with a new perspective of the world and society.
api-1  | Is there anything else which you would like to share with us
api-1  | which would help us understand you better?
api-1  | No
